The paper deals with game-theoretic issues in sponsored search auctions, which falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). It also involves search engine optimization and user behavior modeling, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR). The algorithmic aspect of the paper suggests that it could also be classified under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of machine learning techniques to model user behavior could place it under machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
